<body>
Reports  a JavaScript access to DOM nodes as text using the <code>innerHTML</code> property.
Most usages of <code>innerHTML</code> are performed better with explicit
DOM calls, such as <code>getElementByID()</code> and
<code>createElement()</code>.  Additionally,
<code>innerHTML</code> will not work with XML
DOMs, including DOMs for XHTML if viewed as XML.  This can lead to difficulties in
diagnosing bugs.
